other_tests.findings: Normal-size kidneys, no hydronephrosis, no evidence of renal stones. Right kidney 9.3 cm, left kidney 9.4 cm.
other_tests.changes_over_time: No residual fluid seen within the urinary bladder after voiding.

other_tests.findings: Normal glomeruli with focal mild mesangial hypercellularity; slight segmental linear staining for IgG and albumin; diffusely thin glomerular basement membranes.
other_tests.changes_over_time: No evidence of progressive renal disease two years after the biopsy.

other_tests.findings: 20 to 50 red cells per high-power field and 1+ proteinuria, with dysmorphic red cells and two cellular casts thought to be red-cell casts.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Intermittent hematuria and mild proteinuria persisted.

other_tests.findings: Contained 1152 mg of creatinine and 160 mg of protein.
